      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "government"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "government"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是 the public authority that runs a country or city and organizes public decisions，政府、公共管理机构。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 53,
      "start": 450.927,
      "end": 461.119,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "government"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "在这课里它不是政治讨论，而是 large public project organizer。课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "the government will be building new hotels"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 54,
      "start": 461.469,
      "end": 470.909,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "government"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "因为 hotels, roads, railway lines, and stadiums 都不是一个人能随便完成的小事，需要公共规划和很多团队合作。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 55,
      "start": 471.259,
