      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "stadium"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是 a large sports building or open structure where many people watch events，体育场。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 58,
      "start": 485.076,
      "end": 492.08,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "stadium"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "an immense stadium"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "immense"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是 very large，非常巨大。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 59,
      "start": 492.43,
      "end": 501.59,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "stadium"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "你可以把 school sports field 想象成小版本；Olympic stadium 是能容纳大量观众、运动员和设备的大型场馆。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 60,
      "start": 501.94,
      "end": 504.788,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "design"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第三个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "design"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 61,
      "start": 505.138,
      "end": 506.674,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "design"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "design"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 62,
      "start": 507.023,
      "end": 515.871,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "design"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "design"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是 plan how a building or object will look and work before it is made，设计。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 63,
      "start": 516.221,
      "end": 521.529,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "design"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文说："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "The fantastic modern buildings have been designed by Kurt Gunter."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 64,
      "start": 521.879,
      "end": 530.879,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "design"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "先有 architect or designer 的 plan，后有 workers 按照设计把 buildings 建起来。所以 design 连接了想法和真实建筑。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 65,
      "start": 531.229,
      "end": 544.289,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的 grammar 要像 project manager 一样看。第一类是 future event："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "The Olympic Games will be held in our country."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "还有"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "the whole area will be called 'Olympic City'."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 66,
      "start": 544.638,
      "end": 555.146,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "will be held"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "和"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "will be called"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "都是 future passive，重点是“事情将会发生，区域将会被叫作某个名字”。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 67,
      "start": 555.496,
      "end": 564.832,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二类是 future work in progress："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "will be visiting"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "will be building"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "will be watching"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 68,
      "start": 565.182,
      "end": 573.862,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这些形式让未来变成一段持续画面：visitors will be visiting，government will be building，everybody will be watching。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 69,
      "start": 574.212,
      "end": 581.012,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第三类是 future deadline："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Workers will have completed the new roads by the end of this year."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 70,
      "start": 581.361,
      "end": 586.701,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "还有："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "By the end of next year, they will have finished work on the new stadium."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 71,
      "start": 587.051,
      "end": 595.887,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "will have completed"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "和"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "will have finished"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "的意思是：到那个未来截止时间，事情已经做完。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 72,
      "start": 596.237,
      "end": 609.86,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "最后两句是 already and never before："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "The buildings have been designed."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "说明已经被设计好了；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "the Games have never been held before in this country"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "说明这是第一次。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 73,
      "start": 610.21,
      "end": 624.21,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "所以语法板很清楚：future event, future work, future deadline, already designed, never before。The Games are four years away, but the city must be built step by step before then。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 74,
      "start": 624.56,
      "end": 633.24,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "现在把这课放进你的生活。想象 your school open day will be held next month，很多 parents and visitors 会来学校。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 75,
      "start": 633.59,
      "end": 644.11,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "你要像一个 small project planner 一样解释：what will be held, who will be visiting, what people will be preparing, and what will have been finished by a deadline。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 76,
      "start": 644.46,
      "end": 649.06,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "you_too",
      "scene_meta": {},
